## Checklist for README Creation

Before considering a README complete, verify:

- [ ] Tone is professional and academic; no "obvious", "critical", or filler phrases.
- [ ] Required sections are present in the specified order (title, overview, prerequisites if needed, usage, etc.).
- [ ] Headings use consistent level and capitalization; icons used sparingly and consistently.
- [ ] All code blocks have a language tag and are runnable or clearly marked as examples.
- [ ] Any API is documented with endpoint, parameters table, response structure, and sample.
- [ ] All file and folder references use relative paths and clickable links where appropriate.
- [ ] No secrets or real API keys in the README.
